# Reticle Grid Pattern

The canonical layout system for Agent Machines landing sections. Every section
is a structural grid of hoverable cells with hairline borders, rounded cards
inside cells, full-width separator lines, and hatched margins.

## Page-level structure

```
[outer] [gutter 4rem] [hatch margin 4rem] [content max-w] [hatch margin 4rem] [gutter 4rem] [outer]
```

- **Content**: centered, capped at `--ret-content-max` (1200px).
- **Margins**: `--ret-rail-offset` (4rem) wide, filled with 45deg hatch
  (`repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, var(--ret-rail) 0 1px, transparent 1px 6px)`).
- **Gutters**: same width as margins, empty, bordered on their inner edge.
- Page root has `overflow-x-hidden` to clip full-bleed hairlines.

## Grid construction

Sections use CSS Grid with a narrow auto-width left column + N equal columns:

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-4 auto-rows-auto md:grid-cols-[auto_repeat(8,1fr)]">
```

- Column 1 (`auto`): narrow rail for navigation/tool icons.
- Columns 2–9 (`1fr` each): content cells.
- Mobile collapses to `grid-cols-4`, hiding rail and rightmost cells.

## Cell anatomy

Every cell uses the `Cell` component:

```tsx
<Cell action="..." agent={agent} hue={hue} className="..." hoverVisual={...}>
  {children}
</Cell>
```

- **Borders**: `border-b border-r border-[var(--ret-border)]` — hairline on
  bottom and right. Last column in a row gets `!border-r-0`. Last row gets
  `!border-b-0`. This prevents doubled borders at edges.
- **Hover**: every cell (including empty ones) has a hover overlay with:
  - A visual effect (`HoverHatch`, `HoverGlow`, `HoverPulseGrid`,
    `HoverScene`, `HoverGradient`).
  - An agent action label (logo + monospaced text + pulsing dot) in the
    bottom-left corner, colored in the active agent's hue.

## Cards inside cells

Content cells contain a rounded card with padding:

```tsx
<Cell ...>
  <div className="h-full p-1.5">
    <div className="h-full rounded-lg border border-[var(--ret-border)] bg-[var(--ret-bg)]">
      {/* content */}
    </div>
  </div>
</Cell>
```

- Padding: `p-1.5` (6px) around the card.
- Card: `rounded-lg border border-[var(--ret-border)] bg-[var(--ret-bg)]`.
- 3D viewports use `bg-[var(--ret-bg-soft)]` and add corner cross marks.
- Empty decorative cells also get cards (empty `<div />` with the same classes).

## Full-width hairlines

For section-spanning horizontal lines (like above/below the heading band),
use absolute-positioned divs inside a cell:

```tsx
<div
  className="pointer-events-none absolute top-0 z-30 h-px"
  style={{ left: "-50vw", width: "200vw", background: "var(--ret-border)" }}
/>
```

- `200vw` width + `left: -50vw` guarantees full coverage regardless of cell
  position.
- Cells adjacent to these lines must remove their own `border-b` or
  `border-t` with `!border-b-0` / `!border-t-0` to prevent doubling.

## Border deduplication rules

| Position | Rule |
|---|---|
| Last column in row | `!border-r-0` |
| Last row in grid | `!border-b-0` |
| Adjacent to full-bleed hairline | Remove the matching `border-t` or `border-b` |
| Row-spanning cells | Remove borders on sides that overlap with neighbor cells |

## Hover visual primitives

| Name | Effect |
|---|---|
| `HoverHatch` | Repeating diagonal lines (configurable angle) |
| `HoverGlow` | Radial gradient from center |
| `HoverGradient` | Directional gradient from corner |
| `HoverPulseGrid` | Dot grid + glowing pulsing orb |
| `HoverScene` | Full 3D wireframe scene filling the cell |

All hover effects are tinted in the active agent's hue so they change color
when the agent cycles.

## Agent rail

The left column contains contextual content:

- **Tool cluster cells** (rows without the heading): show a category label +
  2×2 grid of `ServiceIcon` logos (e.g. Automate, Code, Data, Observe).
- **Agent selector** (rows aligned with the heading): a flex column of 5
  agent cards inside a single row-spanning cell. Each agent card is
  `rounded-lg border` with colored border + tinted bg when active.

## Color system

All colors use `var(--ret-*)` tokens. Agent-specific colors come from
`AGENT_HUE` and are applied via inline `style` (not Tailwind classes) since
they're dynamic per-agent values. Never hardcode hex values for borders or
backgrounds — always use the token or the hue variable.

## Do NOT

- Use `border-dashed` — all borders are solid hairlines.
- Add padding to the grid container — cells fill edge-to-edge.
- Use `overflow-hidden` on the hero wrapper (breaks full-bleed lines).
- Mix `style={{}}` with Tailwind for static values — use Tailwind for static,
  `style` only for dynamic agent hue colors.
- Create cells without hover behavior — every cell, even empty ones, must
  have a `hoverVisual` and an `action` string.
